Shipments of products by Canadianmanufacturers declined by 1.5 pct in January to 21.08 billiondlrs, seasonally adjusted, led by a slowdown in transportationequipment, Statistics Canada said.    In December orders rose 2.8 pct.    The federal agency said new orders fell 4.0 pct following a4.5 pct increase in December.    Inventories fell to 33.71 billion dlrs from 34.00 billiondlrs the previous month.            Reuter&#3;